cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "riemann-venue: a machine-checked workspace for the finite-place spectral geometry of divisibility"
message: >-
  If you use this repository — the Kakutani dichotomy formalization, the
  gcd-kernel spectral instruments, the primorial bound, or the open-problem
  dossiers — please cite it as below.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Rodriguez
    given-names: Daniel
notes: >-
  Created by Daniel Rodriguez in collaboration with two AI systems:
  Claude Fable 5 (Anthropic), which co-developed the Lean formalizations,
  computational experiments, and research notes in interactive sessions
  under the author's direction; and GPT 5.5 Pro (OpenAI), which provided
  feedback on the accompanying essay and the repository's initial outline.
  All mathematical content is machine-checked (Lean 4 / Mathlib, zero-sorry
  CI policy, axiom audits) or explicitly labeled otherwise in
  docs/status-ledger.md; correctness rests on the Lean kernel and the
  reproducibility scripts, not on trust in any author, human or artificial.
keywords:
  - Riemann Hypothesis
  - gcd kernel
  - Kakutani dichotomy
  - Lean 4
  - Mathlib
  - formalization
  - GCD sums
repository-code: "https://github.com/idolum-ai/riemann-venue"
